Returns: The state key that the delete operation was applied to.

ClassDesc: Result delivered when app state data has been deleted. Possible status codes include: @B_com#google#android#gms#appstate#AppStateStatusCodes#STATUS_OK_E@ if data was successfully deleted from the server. @B_com#google#android#gms#appstate#AppStateStatusCodes#STATUS_NETWORK_ERROR_OPERATION_FAILED_E@ if the device was unable to communicate with the network. In this case, the operation is not retried automatically. @B_com#google#android#gms#appstate#AppStateStatusCodes#STATUS_CLIENT_RECONNECT_REQUIRED_E@ if the client needs to reconnect to the service to access this data. @B_com#google#android#gms#appstate#AppStateStatusCodes#STATUS_INTERNAL_ERROR_E@ if an unexpected error occurred in the service.
